task.summary: Moves changed to require a call to initialize method. THis is necessary as startpos and starttime cannot be known in advance but moves are created in advance.
Fix a few bugs. System does not work yet. Many failures... :-(
Fixed old calib that was used to test height-diff of P1 and P2. This is one of the things that fucked it all up.

Introduced dev-mode. When this is on the system is initialized with dev parameters. Calib-object is now a singleton. It can be created in only two ways. by loadCalib or createCalib -methods. Motorgroup is now initialized with the default tacho-offsets corresponding to restpoint at M1.
Now it works!? Must be the previous commit that fixed it cause this one dosen't really change anything. nevermind - IT WORKS AGAIN!!!!! :-)
